00:29:49.180 --> 00:29:50.590
Is something about Caravaggio

00:29:50.590 --> 00:29:53.010
and Titian using the
realism in their work.

00:29:53.010 --> 00:29:56.670
And showing things, portraying
as they are, more than creating

00:29:56.670 --> 00:29:59.860
like things that are
kind of a fantasy world.

00:29:59.860 --> 00:30:03.120
We're also going to
see that with the food.

00:30:03.120 --> 00:30:06.360
And then we have these,
some of the influences

00:30:06.360 --> 00:30:09.000
that to start coming
into the United States.

00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:12.840
And we look at the different
influences on Italian architecture.

00:30:12.840 --> 00:30:15.000
And things that our
Presidents were looking at.

00:30:15.000 --> 00:30:17.790
And, as Domenica mentioned
earlier, definitely the food

00:30:17.790 --> 00:30:19.120
and the wine of Jefferson.

00:30:19.120 --> 00:30:22.930
And there are even these clips
that you can find, of the influence

00:30:22.930 --> 00:30:26.180
that Jefferson was
under, of the Italians.

00:30:26.180 --> 00:30:27.880
&gt;&gt; Domenica Marchetti: And he
had a winemaker who was Italian.

