So Lucca is in Tuscany.

00:32:56.450 --> 00:32:58.470
And what he ate would
have been known, he was --

00:32:58.470 --> 00:33:02.370
would have been known as Lucchese,
or the specific food from his town.

00:33:02.370 --> 00:33:06.270
So here we see some more
examples of Tuscan food.

00:33:06.270 --> 00:33:08.760
And then, because it
was a feudal town,

00:33:08.760 --> 00:33:10.310
and it was known for its wealth.

00:33:10.310 --> 00:33:13.620
Later on, when it started
going through economic decline,

00:33:13.620 --> 00:33:17.770
this is really when this term,
the cucina povera got coined,

00:33:17.770 --> 00:33:19.090 position:56%
and people started talking about it.

00:33:19.090 --> 00:33:22.280
Because it was happening at the
same time as the mass immigration,

00:33:22.280 --> 00:33:23.580
then it got brought here.

00:33:23.580 --> 00:33:24.900
And then anything that
came, you know,

00:33:24.900 --> 00:33:26.730
with these poor people, was poor.

00:33:26.730 --> 00:33:30.050
And a lot of times what
was Italian was poor,

00:33:30.050 --> 00:33:31.810
because it was coming with people.

00:33:31.810 --> 00:33:34.310
But when it went around, you
know, through the opera starts

00:33:34.310 --> 00:33:36.740
and through the other things, then
it had a different connotation.

00:33:36.740 --> 00:33:38.040
And also, it's important

00:33:38.040 --> 00:33:40.760 position:56%
to note some very simple
ingredients, like beans, like wheat.

00:33:40.760 --> 00:33:43.920
Fava beans, for example,
world's oldest agricultural crop.

00:33:43.920 --> 00:33:47.220
Cheap as could be,
plentiful, and easy to find.

00:33:47.220 --> 00:33:49.870
But they were, you know,
very expensive at the time.

00:33:49.870 --> 00:33:51.170
They were a currency.

00:33:51.170 --> 00:33:52.610
Lentils were a currency, they
were worth their weight in gold.

00:33:52.610 --> 00:33:54.470 position:56%
So things change at different times.

00:33:54.470 --> 00:33:57.500
And I like to be very careful
about what I call poor and rich,

00:33:57.500 --> 00:33:59.000
because it's all in the matter
of the way you look at it.

00:33:59.000 --> 00:34:00.300
Plus, if it's good for you,

00:34:00.300 --> 00:34:02.800
then it has a wealth, I
